    "target_molecule": "L-Valine",
    "overall_strategy": "The synthesis network for L-Valine follows the experimentally demonstrated cyanosulfidic protometabolism in surface environments (Patel et al., 2015), starting from simple precursors like HCN, H2S, NH3, and sugar derivatives. Upstream, formaldehyde is sourced from hydrothermal CO2 reduction via Fischer-Tropsch-type chemistry on magnetite, enabling Hydrothermal \u2192 Surface flow. In surface pools, formose reactions on borate minerals produce dihydroxyacetone (DHA) and hydroxyacetone (HA) from the glycolaldehyde hub, which undergo Cu/H2S-mediated deoxygenation to the central acetone hub. From acetone, cyanohydrin and thioamide intermediates lead to convergent C5 and speculative C6 \u03b1-hydroxynitrile pathways, followed by amination and hydrolysis to valine. This creates redundancy with 10 pathways varying upstream routes and branches, addressing literature challenges like precursor availability through environmental interconnection. Valine flows to Biochemical environments for peptide assembly on clays, completing the network.",
